title: South Dakota Pheasant Tally
text:
October 18, 2015, 8:04 AM by Perry Groten PIERRE, SD - 
Many hunters enjoyed success in the fields Saturday on the first day of pheasant season in South Dakota. 
According the the South Dakota Game, Fish & Parks Department, In central South Dakota, the average bird count per hunter ranged from one bird to one-and-a-half to two birds in Lyman and Hughes counties. 
In northeast South Dakota, the average bird count was less than one bird in the east, to one-and-a-half to two birds in Edmunds and Faulk counties. 
In the southeast, the average count was one-half to one-and-a-half birds with Beadle, Aurora and Jerauld counties offering the best hunting there. 
And in western South Dakota, hunters averaged from one-half to one bird across the region. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
